                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d363">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European War 1939/2558: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-05-02T12:00:00+02:00"
                            >May 2, 1944—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received May 2—7:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3574. This refers to Department’s 3487, May 1, 5 p.m.<note n="59"
                        xml:id="d363fn59">Not printed.</note> Foreign Office instructed British
                    Embassy to inform you that the release of the tripartite statement on satellite
                    countries had been held up at the request of the Cabinet in order that it might
                    be given further consideration. <pb facs="0617" n="603" xml:id="pg_603"/> I
                    understand that in spite of previous acceptance by the Foreign Office there are
                    certain passages in the statement which the Cabinet feels should be changed. The
                    Cabinet is considering the text of the statement this afternoon and Foreign
                    Office promises to give me the suggested changes as soon as possible whereupon
                    they will be urgently telegraphed to the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Winant</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
